parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the engine to stall, the vehicle to become difficult or impossible to start, and the instrument panel to malfunction, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The key does not turn in the ignition
the engine stalls
the instrument panel malfunctions
the vehicle is difficult or impossible to start
the vehicle will not turn off properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the alternator can cause the vehicle to shut down completely, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The headlights go out
the vehicle shuts down completely
the alternator fails without warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Passlock system can cause the vehicle to become locked, making it difficult or impossible to access the vehicle, which can lead to inconvenience and potential safety risks.
symptoms: The vehicle becomes locked
the anti-theft system malfunctions
the driver is locked out of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A vehicle fire can cause damage to the vehicle, injury to the occupants, and potential fatalities.
symptoms: Smoke coming from the hood of the car
the car becoming engulfed in flames.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS system can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or near-misses, especially in wet weather conditions.
symptoms: The ABS light comes on
the brakes make a funny noise
the brakes clunk several times when the vehicle is first started
the brakes feel spongy
the vehicle experiences extended stopping distance
the vehicle slides when applying brakes in wet weather.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake booster can cause the vehicle to lose braking power, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The brake pedal travels to the floor
the vehicle experiences extended stopping distance
the vehicle accelerates unexpectedly
making it hard to stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of brake components, such as the front brake discs, can cause the vehicle to vibrate or throb when applying brakes, leading to reduced braking performance.
symptoms: The front brake discs are of inferior quality
the vehicle throbs when applying brakes
the brakes need to be replaced prematurely.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ECU can cause the vehicle to accelerate unexpectedly, making it hard to stop, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates up to 70 mph
making it hard to stop
the ECU is faulty
the solenoid is bad.

symptoms: Coolant leaking from underneath the vehicle
engine overheating
check engine light and low coolant light illumination
abnormal engine idle
and accelerated vehicle speed.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Failure Due to Fuel System Component Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of fuel system components can cause the engine to knock, leading to engine failure, which can result in costly repairs, safety risks, and potential accidents.
symptoms: Engine knocking
engine light illumination
fuel smell

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission coolant leak can cause the transmission to fail, leading to costly repairs, safety risks, and potential accidents.
symptoms: Coolant leaking from underneath the vehicle
low coolant light illumination

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Power Rack and Pinion Assembly Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power rack and pinion assembly can cause loss of steering control, making it difficult or impossible to steer the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The steering wheel shakes or vibrates
the steering wheel is loose or feels tight
the vehicle pulls to one side while driving
grinding or knocking noise from the steering system
leakage of power steering fluid
difficulty steering

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering shaft or column can cause the steering wheel to become loose or fall off, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The steering wheel is loose or feels detached
the steering wheel shakes or vibrates

the steering wheel does not return to its normal position.
